_at": "2023-03-21T01:46:13Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The core functionality and file handling of my App is done inside Rust with a Swift / Metal layer on top to handle user input.\r\n\r\nAll works well except the access to the iCloud / Documents folder, i.e. the container returned by\r\n\r\n```swift\r\nvar containerUrl: URL? {\r\n  return FileManager.default.url(forUbiquityContainerIdentifier: nil)?.appendingPathComponent(\"Documents\")\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is done in Swift and I pass the URL to the Rust library.\r\n\r\nThis container is the only one where a sandboxed Mac / iOS app has read / write access to by default, so it is hard to avoid.\r\n\r\nIt seems that code in Rust cannot correctly write to the iCloud directory because of symlinks ? If I create a directory in this container in Rust, I cannot access it. If I create a directory from Swift I can.\r\n\r\nHowever as I want to be able to handle file access in my App from Rust in a cross platform way I would love to have a solution for this. \r\n\r\nSorry if this is not the right place to ask / submit this.", "closed_by": {"login": "markusmoenig", "id": 10293923, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwMjkzOTIz", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10293923?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/markusmoenig", "html_url": "https://github.com/markusmoenig", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/markusmoenig/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/markusmoenig/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/markusmoenig/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/markusmoenig/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/markusmoenig/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/markusmoenig/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/markusmoenig/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/markusmoenig/events{/